## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points
1. **Technique confusion** - Users overwhelmed by multiple methods (stamping, foil, hand-painting, stickers, real lace fabric); unsure which produces best results or fits their skill level
2. **Foil transfer failures** - Foil not adhering properly, patchy coverage, crinkling under topcoat; confusion about correct glue dry time (tacky vs fully dry)
3. **Stamping precision** - Difficulty achieving clean lace pattern pickup from plate; smudged transfers, incomplete designs, alignment issues when placing on nail
4. **Pattern placement** - Uncertainty about where to position lace (full coverage, accent nails, French overlay); fear of looking "too busy" or bridal rather than Valentine romantic
5. **Topcoat disasters** - Topcoat shrinking/shattering foil designs, making stamped patterns cloudy, or removing delicate hand-painted lace; struggle finding compatible sealer

### User Sentiment
Aspirational but intimidated—users admire intricate lace aesthetics but fear technique complexity. Want salon-quality results without advanced skills. Craving clear method comparisons to make informed choice.

